00:26:51.525 --> 00:26:52.706 align:middle line:90%
- For what, Cooper?

00:26:52.706 --> 00:26:55.562 align:middle line:90%


00:26:55.562 --> 00:26:57.000 align:middle line:90%
- To save the world.

00:26:57.000 --> 00:27:01.860 align:middle line:90%


00:27:01.860 --> 00:27:04.920 align:middle line:84%
All of this is one
little girl's bedroom.

00:27:04.920 --> 00:27:08.140 align:middle line:84%
Every moment is
infinitely complex.

00:27:08.140 --> 00:27:10.540 align:middle line:84%
They have access to
infinite time and space,

00:27:10.540 --> 00:27:12.505 align:middle line:84%
but they're not
bound by anything.

00:27:12.505 --> 00:27:16.690 align:middle line:84%
If they can find a
specific place in time,

00:27:16.690 --> 00:27:19.162 align:middle line:90%
they can communicate.

00:27:19.162 --> 00:27:20.476 align:middle line:90%
That's why I'm here.

00:27:20.476 --> 00:27:22.170 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to find a
way to tell Murph,

00:27:22.170 --> 00:27:23.420 align:middle line:90%
just like I found this moment.

00:27:23.420 --> 00:27:24.875 align:middle line:90%
- How, Cooper?

00:27:24.875 --> 00:27:26.377 align:middle line:90%
- Love, TARS, love.

00:27:26.377 --> 00:27:27.630 align:middle line:90%
This is [INAUDIBLE] go inside.

00:27:27.630 --> 00:27:30.300 align:middle line:84%
My connection with Murph,
it is quantifiable.

00:27:30.300 --> 00:27:31.240 align:middle line:90%
It's the key.

00:27:31.240 --> 00:27:34.040 align:middle line:90%
- What are we here to do?

00:27:34.040 --> 00:27:35.516 align:middle line:90%
- Find how to tell her.

00:27:35.516 --> 00:27:38.468 align:middle line:90%


00:27:38.468 --> 00:27:39.452 align:middle line:90%
The watch.

00:27:39.452 --> 00:27:42.896 align:middle line:90%


00:27:42.896 --> 00:27:45.356 align:middle line:90%
The watch.

00:27:45.356 --> 00:27:48.010 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

00:27:48.010 --> 00:27:48.810 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:27:48.810 --> 00:27:50.184 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: So what
he finds out here

00:27:50.184 --> 00:27:53.745 align:middle line:84%
is that the future
advanced humans do

00:27:53.745 --> 00:27:55.620 align:middle line:84%
have the ability to
transcend time and space,

00:27:55.620 --> 00:27:57.720 align:middle line:84%
but they need a medium
still to communicate.

00:27:57.720 --> 00:27:59.970 align:middle line:84%
So what Cooper has to do is
to find that medium, which

00:27:59.970 --> 00:28:02.985 align:middle line:84%
is a specific moment in time
to which he can translate

00:28:02.985 --> 00:28:04.710 align:middle line:84%
through this binary
code, but it's not

00:28:04.710 --> 00:28:06.660 align:middle line:84%
going to work unless
there's love there.

00:28:06.660 --> 00:28:09.690 align:middle line:84%
And what's amazing about that
is that initially in the film

00:28:09.690 --> 00:28:12.330 align:middle line:84%
gravity is the enemy
that has to be overcome.

00:28:12.330 --> 00:28:14.230 align:middle line:84%
Gravity's going
to kill humanity.

00:28:14.230 --> 00:28:16.470 align:middle line:84%
Here gravity is
transformed into the force

00:28:16.470 --> 00:28:19.230 align:middle line:84%
of love, which, believe or
not, that echoes Aristotle.

00:28:19.230 --> 00:28:21.576 align:middle line:84%
Aristotle said that there
is some universal force.

00:28:21.576 --> 00:28:23.700 align:middle line:84%
It causes all the planets
and the celestial spheres

00:28:23.700 --> 00:28:24.692 align:middle line:90%
to spin and go around.

00:28:24.692 --> 00:28:25.650 align:middle line:90%
And what is that force?

00:28:25.650 --> 00:28:26.454 align:middle line:90%
Love.

00:28:26.454 --> 00:28:28.620 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: That's exactly
what this movie is saying.

00:28:28.620 --> 00:28:31.410 align:middle line:84%
And that's how Murph
transcends being

00:28:31.410 --> 00:28:33.180 align:middle line:84%
caught in the black
hole, which surely

00:28:33.180 --> 00:28:34.740 align:middle line:90%
would have ripped him apart.

00:28:34.740 --> 00:28:37.650 align:middle line:84%
And the one thing I like about
this tesseract scene the most

00:28:37.650 --> 00:28:41.130 align:middle line:90%
is that Nolan eschews using CGI.

00:28:41.130 --> 00:28:44.010 align:middle line:84%
He's literally building the set,
probably on a huge soundstage

00:28:44.010 --> 00:28:46.750 align:middle line:84%
somewhere, and using a real
camera to glide in [INAUDIBLE]..

00:28:46.750 --> 00:28:47.790 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: And a real tesseract
that they [INAUDIBLE]

00:28:47.790 --> 00:28:49.123 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: And a real tesseract.

00:28:49.123 --> 00:28:51.215 align:middle line:90%
It is a real tesseract.

00:28:51.215 --> 00:28:52.890 align:middle line:84%
And he does this
throughout the film.

00:28:52.890 --> 00:28:54.960 align:middle line:84%
He uses physical effects,
and he gives the film

00:28:54.960 --> 00:28:59.220 align:middle line:84%
this kind of rough quality that
CGI films really don't have.

00:28:59.220 --> 00:29:00.720 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: That's a good point.

00:29:00.720 --> 00:29:02.700 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: And I'm
with Nolan on that.

00:29:02.700 --> 00:29:03.500 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Yeah.

00:29:03.500 --> 00:29:07.290 align:middle line:84%
The god of this movie is
a future advanced humanity

00:29:07.290 --> 00:29:08.740 align:middle line:90%
united with AI.

00:29:08.740 --> 00:29:11.790 align:middle line:84%
And it's the same idea
that we see in "2001,"

00:29:11.790 --> 00:29:15.090 align:middle line:84%
again with a positive spin
instead of the negative spin.

00:29:15.090 --> 00:29:17.955 align:middle line:84%
And it's fascinating that we
have the crossing of the abyss.

00:29:17.955 --> 00:29:20.330 align:middle line:84%
This is something that comes
out of the esoteric hermetic

00:29:20.330 --> 00:29:21.514 align:middle line:90%
traditions, the idea that--

00:29:21.514 --> 00:29:23.430 align:middle line:84%
what we've seen in "Lord
of the Rings," right?

00:29:23.430 --> 00:29:27.210 align:middle line:84%
Remember, Gandalf had to cross
the abyss, defeat the Balrog,

00:29:27.210 --> 00:29:29.490 align:middle line:84%
and then he moves on to a
higher state of existence.

00:29:29.490 --> 00:29:31.200 align:middle line:84%
The same thing happens
to Cooper, right?

00:29:31.200 --> 00:29:34.800 align:middle line:84%
Cooper has to-- he's the
lone man, the bow man

00:29:34.800 --> 00:29:39.560 align:middle line:84%
shot out, as you pointed out,
to overcome the abyss of death.

00:29:39.560 --> 00:29:42.900 align:middle line:84%
And it's ultimately,
again, love that does that.

00:29:42.900 --> 00:29:44.520 align:middle line:84%
And what's the
point of this movie?

00:29:44.520 --> 00:29:48.000 align:middle line:84%
Well, it's just to
use technology wisely

00:29:48.000 --> 00:29:52.170 align:middle line:84%
and that we can't divorce
it from the ultimate aspect

00:29:52.170 --> 00:29:53.600 align:middle line:90%
of humanity, which is love.

00:29:53.600 --> 00:29:55.350 align:middle line:10%
>>WEIDNER: Another
thing to be pointed out

00:29:55.350 --> 00:29:58.320 align:middle line:10%
is that tree of
life in the Kabbalah

00:29:58.320 --> 00:30:01.380 align:middle line:10%
is a little bit like a tesseract
in the way it's constructed.

00:30:01.380 --> 00:30:03.780 align:middle line:10%
And there is an abyss
in the tree of life.

00:30:03.780 --> 00:30:04.620 align:middle line:90%
It's called Da'at.

00:30:04.620 --> 00:30:06.720 align:middle line:84%
When you're moving
from Tif'eret to Keter,

00:30:06.720 --> 00:30:08.475 align:middle line:90%
you have to cross the abyss.

00:30:08.475 --> 00:30:12.300 align:middle line:84%
Keter is the ultimate
way where you commune

00:30:12.300 --> 00:30:14.730 align:middle line:90%
with the mind of the Creator.

00:30:14.730 --> 00:30:17.470 align:middle line:84%
But you can't commune with
the mind of the Creator

00:30:17.470 --> 00:30:19.012 align:middle line:84%
until you've gone
through this abyss.

00:30:19.012 --> 00:30:19.811 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Right.

00:30:19.811 --> 00:30:21.750 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Kubrick's
telling us this.

00:30:21.750 --> 00:30:23.640 align:middle line:84%
"Lord of the Rings"
is telling us this.

00:30:23.640 --> 00:30:25.597 align:middle line:90%
And Nolan's telling us this.

00:30:25.597 --> 00:30:27.180 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: So what I
like about this film

00:30:27.180 --> 00:30:31.860 align:middle line:84%
is that, again, we're given a
positive appraisal about what

00:30:31.860 --> 00:30:32.990 align:middle line:90%
we can do with technology.

00:30:32.990 --> 00:30:34.290 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't have to be negative.

00:30:34.290 --> 00:30:39.430 align:middle line:84%
We don't have to be
dissuaded from implementing

00:30:39.430 --> 00:30:41.760 align:middle line:84%
a space program or any
of this kind of stuff.

00:30:41.760 --> 00:30:44.260 align:middle line:84%
Because as long as
we do it wisely,

00:30:44.260 --> 00:30:47.850 align:middle line:84%
it can lead us into
terraforming other worlds.

00:30:47.850 --> 00:30:49.650 align:middle line:84%
And again, the chief
message of the film

00:30:49.650 --> 00:30:53.250 align:middle line:84%
is that if we can maintain
interpersonal relations

00:30:53.250 --> 00:30:56.520 align:middle line:84%
without losing them at the
expense of gaining tech

00:30:56.520 --> 00:30:58.800 align:middle line:84%
dominance, then
we're going to go--

00:30:58.800 --> 00:31:01.110 align:middle line:90%
we're going to go to the stars.

00:31:01.110 --> 00:31:05.010 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: My takeaway is
that the love between Cooper

00:31:05.010 --> 00:31:08.020 align:middle line:84%
and Murph actually end
up saving the world.

00:31:08.020 --> 00:31:09.500 align:middle line:90%
So love conquers all.

00:31:09.500 --> 00:31:12.000 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: So again, I think we
have to look back to Aristotle.

00:31:12.000 --> 00:31:14.100 align:middle line:84%
Because although there's
a lot of good in Plato,

00:31:14.100 --> 00:31:15.720 align:middle line:84%
there's also good
correctives that

00:31:15.720 --> 00:31:18.990 align:middle line:84%
come from Aristotle that
rebuke some of the errors,

00:31:18.990 --> 00:31:20.430 align:middle line:90%
I believe, in Plato.

00:31:20.430 --> 00:31:22.350 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things
that Aristotle said

00:31:22.350 --> 00:31:25.200 align:middle line:84%
was that there is some
sort of unifying force

00:31:25.200 --> 00:31:26.010 align:middle line:90%
that's out there.

00:31:26.010 --> 00:31:29.010 align:middle line:84%
He believed that it was a
god and that it was some kind

00:31:29.010 --> 00:31:30.690 align:middle line:90%
of mind, a universal mind.

00:31:30.690 --> 00:31:32.869 align:middle line:84%
But he didn't just say
it was a universal mind.

00:31:32.869 --> 00:31:34.410 align:middle line:84%
Aristotle literally
said it was love.

00:31:34.410 --> 00:31:36.360 align:middle line:84%
He said that love is
the ultimate force,

00:31:36.360 --> 00:31:39.120 align:middle line:84%
the ultimate unity and
attraction that doesn't just

00:31:39.120 --> 00:31:40.110 align:middle line:90%
move the planets.

00:31:40.110 --> 00:31:44.210 align:middle line:84%
It also moves human virtue,
human emotion, and human will.

00:31:44.210 --> 00:31:45.010 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Yeah.

00:31:45.010 --> 00:31:47.530 align:middle line:84%
And love's that one thing that
really you can't quantify.

00:31:47.530 --> 00:31:48.330 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Right.

00:31:48.330 --> 00:31:51.180 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: You can't explain
why you love your child

00:31:51.180 --> 00:31:53.166 align:middle line:84%
or why you love your
wife or whatever.

00:31:53.166 --> 00:31:54.040 align:middle line:90%
You can't explain it.

00:31:54.040 --> 00:31:55.331 align:middle line:90%
You can't explain why you love.

00:31:55.331 --> 00:31:56.460 align:middle line:90%
You don't know why.

00:31:56.460 --> 00:31:58.720 align:middle line:84%
So it's a completely
mysterious force.

00:31:58.720 --> 00:32:01.550 align:middle line:84%
And again, I believe that
there is this ether around us.

00:32:01.550 --> 00:32:02.350 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Right.

00:32:02.350 --> 00:32:04.920 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: And I believe
that love is a gravity.

00:32:04.920 --> 00:32:07.170 align:middle line:90%
It is a very serious gravity.

00:32:07.170 --> 00:32:11.040 align:middle line:84%
And when you're in a
loving relationship,

00:32:11.040 --> 00:32:12.374 align:middle line:90%
that gravity is very comforting.

00:32:12.374 --> 00:32:14.581 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: I think it's a real
experience of the divine.

